  <static seed="104" source="Contrib/PCC/BasicAlgebra/Factoring/factoring355.pg">
    <statement><p>Factor the given polynomial.</p>
<p><m>{r^{2}+2r+3}=</m> <fillin characters="19" name="AnSwEr0001"/></p>
</statement>
    <answer>
      <p>
        <m>\text{prime}</m>
      </p>
    </answer>
    <solution><p>The number <m>3</m> can be factored into the product of two numbers in the following ways:</p>
<p>\[1(3),-1(-3)\]</p>
<p>Since no pair<rsq/>s sum is <m>2</m>, we conclude that this polynomial is <alert>prime</alert>.</p>
</solution>
